==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kissingcrust
<hw>Kiss"ing*crust`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>The portion of the upper crust of a loaf which
has touched another loaf in baking.</def> <rj><au>Lamb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A massy fragment from the rich <qex>kissingcrust</qex> that hangs
like a fretted cornice from the upper half of the loaf.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Howitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>kissing disease</ent>⟦br⟧
